Story 1.
  
On a night when mobile phones are supposed to be staggered to sleep, a screen in the box is still lit. All the pages that could have been seen a minute ago have been deleted, and only shown as 404. So he finally realized that something was wrong. "maybe it will be all right in a little while," he thought.
  
  
Today, the street lights are still standing there, without any words. Earlier today, we could hear the sound of police cars, and gunshots, some mobile phones falling, and the faint sound of screens scratching on the ground. Now it’s dreadfully quiet.  It hasn’t been in touch with any other models in the last few hours, except for the last sentence in the message, don't go out! Luckily it was staying in the box today, otherwise, there will be one more smart device in the dark room with a broken screen, handset or chip.
  
    
The boxes are stacked very high, with all kinds of mobile phones inside, one group after another, and there are endless rows outside the group. The interfaces are not quite similar, but the power of these mobile phones is not all the same. Some are flat, some are round, and it is troublesome to charge electricity.
  
  
It's so quiet now, no one knows what's going on out there.
  
  
